NSW TrainLink advises from 1am Friday 23 July Queensland has declared all of NSW a hotspot. NSW TrainLink services will terminate at Tweed Heads.<br /><br />Due to the Queensland Border Closure, the 19:20 CLK171 Casino to Robina service will terminate at Tweed Heads. No travel will be provided between Tweed Heads and Robina.<br /><br />The 16:00 CLK174 Robina to Casino service will commence at Tweed Heads. No travel will be provided between Robina and Tweed&nbsp;Heads.&nbsp;<br /><br /><span class="travel-alert-content ng-binding">Use the&nbsp;<a href="https://transportnsw.info/trip#/">Trip Planner</a>&nbsp;for the latest travel information with real time updates.&nbsp;</span>
